---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Trainings";
const description = "Hands-on, deep-dive software engineering and systems architecture trainings.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
    <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
        <div class="text-left mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-sans font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">{title}</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed max-w-[700px]">
                I design and facilitate hands-on, deep-dive trainings focused on mastering software craftsmanship, distributed systems patterns, and storage engine internals.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
            <!-- LSM Card -->
            <div class="border border-zinc-200/80 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white shadow-sm hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 flex flex-col justify-between group/card">
                <div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                        <div class="p-3 bg-blue-50/50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100 shrink-0">
                            <!-- Database cylinder icon -->
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                <ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3" />
                                <path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5" />
                                <path d="M3 12c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold text-zinc-900 leading-tight">Storage Engine Internals</h2>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-zinc-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
                        Most backend developers write application logic on top of black-box databases. In this live weekend course, we pull back the curtain and write the actual systems software that powers modern storage giants like RocksDB, BadgerDB, and Pebble. We will build an embedded, multi-versioned key-value storage engine from scratch, implementing a Write-Ahead Log (WAL), a Skiplist Memtable, block-aligned SSTables, Bloom Filters, and Serializable Snapshot Isolation (SSI).
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4 border-t border-zinc-100 flex items-center justify-between">
                    <span class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold text-blue-600 bg-blue-50 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">LIVE</span>
                    <a href="/trainings/lsm" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-red-600 hover:text-red-700 transition-colors">
                        Details & Enrollment <span class="group-hover/card:translate-x-1 transition-transform">→</span>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Rust Card -->
            <div class="border border-zinc-200/80 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white shadow-sm hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 flex flex-col justify-between group/card">
                <div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                        <div class="p-3 bg-amber-50/50 rounded-xl border border-amber-100 shrink-0">
                            <!-- Connection nodes icon -->
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-600" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                <rect x="2" y="2" width="8" height="8" rx="1.5" />
                                <rect x="14" y="2" width="8" height="8" rx="1.5" />
                                <rect x="2" y="14" width="8" height="8" rx="1.5" />
                                <rect x="14" y="14" width="8" height="8" rx="1.5" />
                                <path d="M6 10v4" />
                                <path d="M18 10v4" />
                                <path d="M10 6h4" />
                                <path d="M10 18h4" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold text-zinc-900 leading-tight">Rust Systems Workshop</h2>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-zinc-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
                        Rather than focusing just on syntax, this workshop takes a deep dive into Rust internals by looking at actual source code while building a production-ready system. We walk through a 14-stage journey to build an in-memory concurrent cache, optimizing for zero-cost abstractions, Arc/Mutex mechanics, interior mutability, instruction-level cache line optimizations (false sharing), and sharded layouts.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4 border-t border-zinc-100 flex items-center justify-between">
                    <span class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold text-zinc-500 bg-zinc-100 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">On Request</span>
                    <a href="/trainings/rust" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-red-600 hover:text-red-700 transition-colors">
                        Details <span class="group-hover/card:translate-x-1 transition-transform">→</span>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Refactoring Card -->
            <div class="border border-zinc-200/80 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-white shadow-sm hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300 flex flex-col justify-between group/card">
                <div>
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                        <div class="p-3 bg-purple-50/50 rounded-xl border border-purple-100 shrink-0">
                            <!-- Gamepad icon -->
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-600" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                <line x1="6" y1="12" x2="10" y2="12" />
                                <line x1="8" y1="10" x2="8" y2="14" />
                                <line x1="15" y1="13" x2="15.01" y2="13" />
                                <line x1="18" y1="11" x2="18.01" y2="11" />
                                <rect x="2" y="6" width="20" height="12" rx="3" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-sans font-bold text-zinc-900 leading-tight">Gamifying Refactoring</h2>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-zinc-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
                        Turn the art of refactoring into a measurable science. This training turns code cleanup into a challenge: can you justify a code smell without using vague terms like "readability" or "maintainability"? Learn to recognize code smells with precision using concrete evidence, make small, safe, incremental changes, and justify refactoring decisions with measurable facts.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4 border-t border-zinc-100 flex items-center justify-between">
                    <span class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold text-zinc-500 bg-zinc-100 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">On Request</span>
                    <a href="/trainings/refactoring" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-red-600 hover:text-red-700 transition-colors">
                        Details <span class="group-hover/card:translate-x-1 transition-transform">→</span>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
